<p>If I was using a loop that looked like this:</p>  <pre><code>String string = "DF3"; for (int i = string.length() - 1; i &gt;= 0; --i) {         int c = string.charAt(i);          convertedHex += (i &lt;&lt; 4);  } </code></pre>  <p>How would I calculate <code>Math.pow(16, i)</code> without using <code>Math.pow()</code>, another loop, or multiplication? Specifically, how can I do it with <strong>only</strong> bitwise operators?</p>